X
Y
\mu(X\cup Y) = \mu(X)+\mu(Y)
\mu(A) = \mu(P\cup (A-P)) = \mu(P)+\mu(A-P)
\mu(B) = \mu(Q\cup(B-Q)) = \mu(Q)+\mu(B-Q)
\mu(A)\lt\mu(B)
\mu(A)
\mu(P)
\mu(Q)
\mu(P)+\mu(A-P)\lt \mu(Q)+\mu(B-Q)
\mu(P)=\mu(Q)
\mu(A-P) \lt \mu(B-Q)
